    "body": "at the moment, this is by design, the caller should check the RPC response when submitting a response, and if the transaction is rejected, it should resubmit it if the error is transient, like when the number of transactions allowed per sender in a given block is reached, because even if you change the limit, there will be always one.\r\nWe are currently working on improving the transaction pool, so thing could improve in the next releases.",
